                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1014: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-06T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 6, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. Reference White’s telephone conversation Thurston this morning.<note n="97"
                        xml:id="d463fn97">See memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State,
                        February 6, <ref target="#pg_453">p. 453</ref>.</note> Telegram just
                    received from Bogotá indicates change in situation and that President Olaya
                    withdraws his acceptance of proposal mentioned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
